info.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 29 at 12:20PM PST until February 01 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Monterey
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 7 AM WEDNESDAY TO 4 AM PST THURSDAY... * WHAT...South winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 50 mph expected. * WHERE...Portions of California. * WHEN...From 7 AM Wednesday to 4 AM PST Thursday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Wind gusts up to 50 mph are possible along ridge tops and the highest elevations. Specifically for the Santa Lucia Mountains, highest gusts could reach 60 mph. In lower elevations along the immediate coast, gusts of 30 to 40 mph are expected. Take care to secure loose outdoor items that can easily be blown over such as furniture and decorations.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
